# Real-Time Ranking Consistency

- Treat sentiment/profile ranking as a swappable provider module. Do not hardcode one model path in endpoint logic.
- Use centralized ranking methods for action scoring and profile rollups. Endpoint handlers must call shared ranking services, not duplicate score math inline.
- Any code change touching post/action flows must keep ranking updates in sync for relevant actions:
  - post
  - reply
  - repost/share
  - like
  - quote
  - bookmark
  - report
- Profile rank rollups must stay based on the latest 500 action events and include:
  - overall summed score
  - per-action score breakdown
  - provider metadata
- Reporting non-negative/non-toxic content must apply a penalty contribution.
- LLM integrations are optional add-ons; baseline ranking/profile generation must function without LLM modules installed.
